 lead MPs to defect. This book will be of interest to students and lecturers of British politics and anyone interested in the relationship between British political parties in the last century.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 02. Jun 2024) 0aDefectionzGreat BritainxHistoryy20th century. 0aDefectionzGreat BritainxHistoryy21st century. 0aRight and left (Political science)zGreat BritainxHistoryy20th century. 4amanchesterhive variable pricing textbooks. 7aPOLITICAL SCIENCE / American Government / National.2bisacsh  aBritish Government.  aConservatives.  aGreat War.  aLabour Party.  aLiberal Democrats.  aLiberal Party.  adefections.  ainward defector.  aoutward defector.  aparty leadership.  apolitical analysts.1 aWyburn-Powell, Alun, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertManchester University Press 1986 - 2013 eBook Packagez9783111283630oZDB-23-MUP40uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781526130815423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9781526130815/original  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aZDB-23-MUPc1986d2013